1
00:00:29,958 --> 00:00:34,833
"Wooju Bakery."

2
00:00:46,417 --> 00:00:47,958
What the… when did you wake up?

3
00:00:49,917 --> 00:00:51,583
Why are you sleeping in my room?

4
00:00:57,292 --> 00:00:59,750
I had a nightmare last night.

5
00:01:03,042 --> 00:01:06,625
Then why didn't you wake me up? Why were
you just staring at me?

6
00:01:06,750 --> 00:01:12,375
You looked so peaceful when you were
asleep.

7
00:01:12,500 --> 00:01:14,083
And…

8
00:01:14,208 --> 00:01:14,958
And what?

9
00:01:15,083 --> 00:01:16,333
You looked beautiful.

10
00:01:17,083 --> 00:01:20,125
What are you talking about…

11
00:01:20,833 --> 00:01:22,292
My face?

12
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:27,000
You know, don't call me 'Boss' anymore.

13
00:01:27,125 --> 00:01:29,083
Just call me Wooju.

14
00:01:29,417 --> 00:01:30,750
Why?

15
00:01:34,167 --> 00:01:36,833
I don't know… you keep calling me 'Boss'.

16
00:01:36,958 --> 00:01:38,750
It makes it feel like we're only connected
by money.

17
00:01:38,875 --> 00:01:42,750
But isn't that exactly what we are?

18
00:01:46,208 --> 00:01:47,375
Listen to me.

19
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:50,542
Don't call me 'Boss' ever again.

20
00:01:51,500 --> 00:01:52,708
Got it?

21
00:01:58,083 --> 00:01:59,625
Wow.

22
00:02:01,917 --> 00:02:05,250
The bread looks really tasty.

23
00:02:05,375 --> 00:02:08,500
My prince is a really good baker, so…

24
00:02:09,125 --> 00:02:13,125
You know… I'm curious.

25
00:02:14,125 --> 00:02:16,667
How did the prince become such a good
baker?

26
00:02:16,792 --> 00:02:20,125
A prince doesn't usually bake bread in his
own palace, right?

27
00:02:21,042 --> 00:02:23,875
Well, when he was a boy, he used to eat
this delicious bread.

28
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:26,000
And he wanted to learn how to make it.

29
00:02:26,125 --> 00:02:28,917
So the King ordered the best royal pastry
chef in the kingdom.

30
00:02:29,042 --> 00:02:30,167
To teach him how to bake.

31
00:02:30,292 --> 00:02:33,792
Oh, so he had a teacher, huh?

32
00:02:33,917 --> 00:02:36,250
He was his his best friend, but then…

33
00:02:36,375 --> 00:02:38,000
he disappeared.

34
00:02:38,417 --> 00:02:40,958
Disappeared? Where?

35
00:02:41,083 --> 00:02:42,375
I don't know.

36
00:02:45,125 --> 00:02:47,667
Hey! Don't touch the bread!

37
00:02:47,792 --> 00:02:50,250
And keep your drool to yourselves. These
are for the customers.

38
00:02:50,375 --> 00:02:51,708
I didn't touch the bread.

39
00:02:51,833 --> 00:02:53,917
Then don't get so close.

40
00:03:01,583 --> 00:03:02,750
Everyone.

41
00:03:02,875 --> 00:03:04,958
Let's work hard and sell out today!

42
00:03:06,292 --> 00:03:07,458
What's with you?

43
00:03:07,583 --> 00:03:10,042
You're not the boss, what are you doing?

44
00:03:10,167 --> 00:03:12,792
It's called taking initiative.

45
00:03:12,917 --> 00:03:14,792
Taking initiative?

46
00:03:15,167 --> 00:03:15,958
Hey.

47
00:03:16,083 --> 00:03:17,667
You guys are just here to pay off your
debts.

48
00:03:18,208 --> 00:03:21,167
What initiative?

49
00:03:22,542 --> 00:03:26,375
"Don't call me 'Boss', call me Wooju."

50
00:03:27,500 --> 00:03:31,583
Who said that?

51
00:03:35,208 --> 00:03:38,167
That's only for when it's just the two of
us…

52
00:03:43,625 --> 00:03:45,375
Thanks.

53
00:03:51,417 --> 00:03:55,417
So you're saying aliens kidnapped you?

54
00:03:55,542 --> 00:03:57,958
I'm telling you, it's true!

55
00:03:58,542 --> 00:04:00,458
When did this happen? I'm not even sure.

56
00:04:00,583 --> 00:04:03,292
I told you, I was kidnapped! My hands and
feet were tied.

57
00:04:03,417 --> 00:04:05,208
And they wrapped me up in plastic wrap…

58
00:04:05,333 --> 00:04:08,042
Oh! And I even called the police.

59
00:04:08,167 --> 00:04:10,000
You called the police?

60
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:10,833
Yes, I did.

61
00:04:10,958 --> 00:04:12,583
And then what happened?

62
00:04:13,583 --> 00:04:15,042
Well…

63
00:04:16,042 --> 00:04:17,042
I don't really remember.

64
00:04:17,167 --> 00:04:18,417
You don't remember?

65
00:04:18,542 --> 00:04:19,875
No, it's just…

66
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,583
The people who kidnapped me…

67
00:04:21,708 --> 00:04:24,458
You might not believe me, but they were
aliens.

68
00:04:24,583 --> 00:04:26,625
No, seriously, they were definitely
aliens.

69
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:28,958
Oh, stop talking nonsense…

70
00:04:30,333 --> 00:04:32,125
Cancel that police report right now.

71
00:04:32,250 --> 00:04:35,917
Hold on, I know you think I'm spewing
nonsense, but…

72
00:04:36,042 --> 00:04:37,792
- I told you!
- But I have my reasons.

73
00:04:37,917 --> 00:04:40,167
I don't like loud noises.

74
00:04:40,625 --> 00:04:41,333
Secretary Lee.

75
00:04:41,458 --> 00:04:42,667
Yes, Chairman.

76
00:04:50,083 --> 00:04:51,542
Good grief…

77
00:05:00,833 --> 00:05:02,333
Keep that video up on YouTube.

78
00:05:02,458 --> 00:05:04,250
I want him completely ruined.

79
00:05:07,042 --> 00:05:08,708
Thank you, sir.

80
00:05:09,375 --> 00:05:10,458
Hmm.

81
00:05:19,542 --> 00:05:19,917
Ms. Mina.

82
00:05:20,042 --> 00:05:21,958
Um… please, stop investigating that
person.

83
00:05:22,083 --> 00:05:25,250
What do you mean by "stop investigating"?

84
00:05:25,375 --> 00:05:28,292
About the alien thing… I misunderstood. I
was just overthinking it.

85
00:05:28,417 --> 00:05:29,708
What are you talking about? We were just…

86
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:32,333
There's no such thing as aliens on Earth!

87
00:05:32,750 --> 00:05:34,000
It's all just conspiracy theories.

88
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:35,417
I understand.

89
00:05:40,083 --> 00:05:43,750
Something feels off… It's like my memory
was wiped.

90
00:05:48,500 --> 00:05:49,500
Let me ask you a question.

91
00:05:49,625 --> 00:05:52,500
Hmm? Let's assume aliens actually exist.

92
00:05:52,625 --> 00:05:54,750
And let's assume they're planning
something on Earth.

93
00:05:54,875 --> 00:05:58,333
What would be their motive for coming
here?

94
00:05:58,458 --> 00:06:01,667
Are they here to commit crimes?

95
00:06:01,792 --> 00:06:03,458
If they're here, they must have a motive,
right?

96
00:06:03,583 --> 00:06:04,583
Think about it.

97
00:06:04,708 --> 00:06:07,833
What kind of advanced aliens would have
the motive to commit crimes?

98
00:06:07,958 --> 00:06:09,000
A motive…

99
00:06:09,125 --> 00:06:13,083
Exactly, a motive! It doesn't make sense,
right?

100
00:06:13,208 --> 00:06:14,375
Exactly!

101
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:16,333
A motive!

102
00:06:18,167 --> 00:06:19,583
Thanks, senior.

103
00:06:20,292 --> 00:06:24,000
Geez… this guy has really lost it.

104
00:06:26,917 --> 00:06:28,375
Thank you for coming!

105
00:06:29,458 --> 00:06:30,708
Take care.

106
00:06:32,167 --> 00:06:35,708
Hey! You're that YouTuber, right?

107
00:06:35,833 --> 00:06:37,292
Come on in!

108
00:06:46,708 --> 00:06:47,958
Hmph.

109
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:50,333
What…

110
00:06:50,458 --> 00:06:51,417
Are you here for?

111
00:06:51,542 --> 00:06:55,958
She's the one who featured us last time,
and we went viral.

112
00:06:56,458 --> 00:07:00,333
That video got 1.2 million views!

113
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:05,042
I'm so sorry about our employee biting
your finger last time.

114
00:07:05,167 --> 00:07:06,667
I'll cover the medical expenses.

115
00:07:06,792 --> 00:07:08,083
Medical expenses…!

116
00:07:08,208 --> 00:07:09,042
Medical expenses?

117
00:07:09,167 --> 00:07:10,958
Is that all you're going to do?

118
00:07:11,083 --> 00:07:13,458
Hachi! Apologize!

119
00:07:15,292 --> 00:07:16,083
I'm sorry.

120
00:07:16,208 --> 00:07:17,958
You're a bad customer!

121
00:07:18,667 --> 00:07:19,792
Seriously…

122
00:07:20,167 --> 00:07:23,708
YouTuber… um… go ahead and start your
livestream.

123
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:27,708
Starting now.

124
00:07:29,125 --> 00:07:33,083
Hey everyone, it's Mina from 'Publicity
TV'.

125
00:07:33,208 --> 00:07:35,042
The response to the last video was
amazing.

126
00:07:35,167 --> 00:07:36,667
So I'm back!

127
00:07:36,792 --> 00:07:39,042
Ta-da! This is Wooju Bakery.

128
00:07:39,167 --> 00:07:42,000
Honestly, this place is weird and not that
great.

129
00:07:42,125 --> 00:07:44,333
But I didn't expect so many comments.

130
00:07:44,458 --> 00:07:47,250
Should I try the bread again and tell you
how it tastes?

131
00:07:49,667 --> 00:07:51,042
Here we go!

132
00:07:51,542 --> 00:07:53,000
Try this one.

133
00:07:54,333 --> 00:07:56,958
The bread looks really fancy, right?

134
00:07:57,083 --> 00:07:58,958
But how does it taste?

135
00:08:01,333 --> 00:08:05,917
Hmm… this taste… this…!

136
00:08:06,958 --> 00:08:08,208
Ah!

137
00:08:08,833 --> 00:08:09,667
What a liar!

138
00:08:09,792 --> 00:08:11,792
What a bad customer!

139
00:08:13,125 --> 00:08:14,958
Air, you try a bite too.

140
00:08:15,083 --> 00:08:17,167
Oh! Please, stop messing around!

141
00:08:17,292 --> 00:08:18,542
Hey! Stop!

142
00:08:19,542 --> 00:08:21,333
Don't eat it!

143
00:08:22,375 --> 00:08:23,792
Hey!

144
00:08:24,167 --> 00:08:25,667
What if something happens to you?

145
00:08:29,083 --> 00:08:29,917
Raon!

146
00:08:30,042 --> 00:08:32,042
What on earth did you put in this bread!

147
00:08:32,875 --> 00:08:35,333
I heard Earthlings love alcohol…

148
00:08:35,458 --> 00:08:37,417
So I tried making alcohol bread.

149
00:08:45,625 --> 00:08:47,208
Was it too strong?

150
00:08:48,208 --> 00:08:49,500
Wake up.

151
00:08:50,000 --> 00:08:53,167
Ah… my head hurts.

152
00:08:53,292 --> 00:08:54,583
What's going on?

153
00:08:54,708 --> 00:08:58,042
I'm sorry, the bread you just ate had
alcohol in it.

154
00:08:58,167 --> 00:09:00,625
Alcohol… alcohol bread?

155
00:09:00,750 --> 00:09:02,958
I can't drink a single drop of alcohol!

156
00:09:03,250 --> 00:09:04,500
I'm sorry.

157
00:09:04,625 --> 00:09:06,708
Then try this bread instead.

158
00:09:07,292 --> 00:09:08,792
What is this?

159
00:09:09,833 --> 00:09:12,125
Hangover cure bread.
You'll sober up immediately.

160
00:09:12,250 --> 00:09:15,750
My stomach hurts so much. Can I even eat
that right now?

161
00:09:16,292 --> 00:09:19,542
You can that bread as your suppository,
don't worry.

162
00:09:19,667 --> 00:09:21,250
I've tried it once before.

163
00:09:21,375 --> 00:09:23,917
Hey! Keep it down! Get out!

164
00:09:24,042 --> 00:09:26,500
I can't stand either of you.

165
00:09:26,792 --> 00:09:29,417
So our contract is over just like that?

166
00:09:29,542 --> 00:09:31,042
Does that mean I don't have to pay you
back?

167
00:09:31,875 --> 00:09:33,208
Who said you didn't have to pay me back?

168
00:09:33,333 --> 00:09:34,333
Just get out of my sight for now.

169
00:09:34,458 --> 00:09:36,875
Get out for an hour and then come back!

170
00:09:37,792 --> 00:09:38,542
Hachi!

171
00:09:38,667 --> 00:09:40,167
Break time.

172
00:09:41,083 --> 00:09:41,917
Let's go out for a bit.

173
00:09:42,042 --> 00:09:43,542
Wait a second…

174
00:09:45,250 --> 00:09:46,792
Good grief…

175
00:09:55,625 --> 00:09:57,000
Are you okay?

176
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:15,458
Hmm?

177
00:10:17,125 --> 00:10:19,375
What is this? I'm actually sober.

178
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:20,958
Really?

179
00:10:22,417 --> 00:10:24,333
I'm really sorry.

180
00:10:29,792 --> 00:10:31,708
Is this supposed to be fun?

181
00:10:33,083 --> 00:10:34,625
You don't think it's fun?

182
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:37,500
Why would it be fun to go back and forth
like this?

183
00:10:37,625 --> 00:10:39,250
What's the concept of this equipment?

184
00:10:39,375 --> 00:10:41,500
Are you trying to make me feel gravity?

185
00:10:46,833 --> 00:10:48,458
Isn't it amazing?

186
00:10:48,583 --> 00:10:51,250
Earthlings play like this when they're
kids.

187
00:10:58,917 --> 00:11:00,375
Prince!

188
00:11:00,750 --> 00:11:03,375
Studying the Earthlings isn't our mission.

189
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:05,875
- Mission?
- What did you just say when you seduced me?

190
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:08,167
You said you were going to Earth for a
special mission.

191
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:10,875
Not running away from that arranged
marriage.

192
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,750
That's what you said, right?

193
00:11:15,583 --> 00:11:18,000
Well, actually…

194
00:11:18,125 --> 00:11:19,333
Was it all a lie?

195
00:11:19,458 --> 00:11:20,625
It's not exactly a lie…

196
00:11:20,750 --> 00:11:22,042
Prince, tell me!

197
00:11:22,167 --> 00:11:24,917
Did you just use me to run away from that
marriage?

198
00:11:25,042 --> 00:11:25,833
I mean…

199
00:11:25,958 --> 00:11:27,500
What are we even doing here?

200
00:11:27,625 --> 00:11:29,542
Why did we come here?

201
00:11:32,250 --> 00:11:35,708
Exactly, that's what I'd like to know.

202
00:11:37,292 --> 00:11:38,375
Welcome to Earth!

203
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:39,000
Do we know each other?

204
00:11:39,125 --> 00:11:42,125
Prince! He's the owner of the exchange
shop who cheated us!

205
00:11:42,250 --> 00:11:46,167
He exchanged our money from the sale of
the two buildings only for 115,000 won!

206
00:11:46,292 --> 00:11:48,667
That's called an exchange rate.

207
00:11:51,417 --> 00:11:52,625
Thank you very much.

208
00:11:52,750 --> 00:11:57,208
Someone has been looking for you.
Follow me, quietly.

209
00:12:01,458 --> 00:12:03,125
My name is Lee Sung-ryong.

210
00:12:03,250 --> 00:12:05,417
I run a small business here on Earth.

211
00:12:05,542 --> 00:12:06,833
Nice to meet you.

212
00:12:09,583 --> 00:12:11,333
You've come a long way. You must be
exhausted.

213
00:12:11,458 --> 00:12:13,375
Yes, we've come such a long way.

214
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:15,083
But…

215
00:12:16,167 --> 00:12:18,250
What do you do for a living?

216
00:12:19,833 --> 00:12:21,583
I am a Prin…

217
00:12:24,083 --> 00:12:27,792
I'm the Bread King.

218
00:12:28,667 --> 00:12:32,125
Why would business people come all the way
to Earth?

219
00:12:32,250 --> 00:12:33,958
The bread on Earth isn't even that good.

220
00:12:39,917 --> 00:12:42,875
I… I'll give you back the money I took.

221
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:44,208
Huh?

222
00:12:44,833 --> 00:12:47,958
I can't let that bakery go under.

223
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:49,750
Let's step outside and talk.

224
00:12:50,333 --> 00:12:52,375
Wait, that hurts! Let go of me!

225
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:54,042
Don't move!

226
00:12:55,667 --> 00:12:56,958
It's the police!

227
00:12:57,458 --> 00:12:58,500
Ms. Mina.

228
00:12:58,625 --> 00:13:00,750
The aliens tried to kidnap you again,
didn't they?

229
00:13:00,875 --> 00:13:02,375
- No, that's not it.
- That's not what happened.

230
00:13:02,500 --> 00:13:04,542
Look, it's really not like that…

231
00:13:07,208 --> 00:13:08,958
Chairman Lee Sung-ryong.

232
00:13:09,417 --> 00:13:11,833
We received a report that you are an
alien.

233
00:13:11,958 --> 00:13:13,625
We're here to investigate.

234
00:13:16,625 --> 00:13:20,458
Aliens? What are you talking about?

235
00:13:20,583 --> 00:13:22,667
We came here because we have the facts.

236
00:13:24,958 --> 00:13:27,542
Who filed such a ridiculous report?

237
00:13:27,667 --> 00:13:29,625
Aliens only exist in sci-fi movies.

238
00:13:29,750 --> 00:13:32,750
How could there be aliens on Earth?

239
00:13:32,875 --> 00:13:33,917
Right?

240
00:13:34,042 --> 00:13:35,917
Everyone, hands up! Against the wall!

241
00:13:36,042 --> 00:13:37,250
Move it!

242
00:13:38,667 --> 00:13:44,833
You look busy, so we'll be going now.

243
00:13:44,958 --> 00:13:47,333
We have bread to bake.

244
00:13:56,208 --> 00:13:57,417
Run!

245
00:14:55,542 --> 00:14:56,708
What's wrong now?

246
00:14:56,833 --> 00:14:59,625
The power unit and communication device
are not working.

247
00:14:59,750 --> 00:15:00,417
Really?

248
00:15:00,542 --> 00:15:04,708
The power unit and communication unit of
the spaceship are also broken.

249
00:15:04,833 --> 00:15:06,375
Shut up.

250
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:08,750
How many more days are you going to waste
on that toy?

251
00:15:08,875 --> 00:15:10,417
If it's broken, just throw it away.

252
00:15:10,542 --> 00:15:14,000
Throwing it away? Do you know how
expensive this is?

253
00:15:14,458 --> 00:15:18,125
How expensive could it be? I'll buy ten
when I get my paycheck.

254
00:15:19,083 --> 00:15:20,875
Boss, are you actually going to pay me?

255
00:15:22,208 --> 00:15:23,750
Yeah.

256
00:15:23,875 --> 00:15:29,292
I wasn't going to pay you a dime
until you paid off your debt.

257
00:15:29,417 --> 00:15:32,167
But you look a bit pathetic… No, wait.

258
00:15:32,292 --> 00:15:34,167
I'm not a heartless boss.

259
00:15:34,292 --> 00:15:36,417
I'll give you half your pay.

260
00:15:36,542 --> 00:15:37,583
Really?

261
00:15:37,708 --> 00:15:38,958
Yeah.

262
00:15:40,292 --> 00:15:41,542
Thanks, Boss!

263
00:15:48,625 --> 00:15:50,458
Go clean up.

264
00:15:52,583 --> 00:15:55,167
Boss, are you gonna pay me, too?

265
00:15:56,250 --> 00:16:01,125
You'll get paid. Now go buy yourself some
clothes.

266
00:16:01,250 --> 00:16:04,625
That's a top notch pilot suit!
Not dull clothes.

267
00:16:04,750 --> 00:16:07,417
Wooju, what is this bread?

268
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:15,417
Prince, it's a Kauncilion!

269
00:16:15,542 --> 00:16:18,167
That's right! A Kauncilion.

270
00:16:18,292 --> 00:16:20,917
Kauncilion? What's that?

271
00:16:21,042 --> 00:16:22,958
It's the name of our home planet.

272
00:16:24,583 --> 00:16:27,792
My dad always called it 'Star Bread'.

273
00:16:27,917 --> 00:16:31,417
Wait, you mean… your dad made this bread?

274
00:16:32,167 --> 00:16:32,667
Yeah.

275
00:16:32,792 --> 00:16:36,625
People from my place would recognize this
bread by its shape.

276
00:16:36,750 --> 00:16:40,583
Wait, your dad must be from my home town?

277
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:48,292
Yeah, your dad is from our home.

278
00:16:49,833 --> 00:16:55,250
Why do you think my dad is from your home?

279
00:16:57,958 --> 00:16:59,667
Because…

280
00:17:02,125 --> 00:17:03,750
I know your father very well.

281
00:17:10,917 --> 00:17:13,792
You're such a liar. Do you really think
I'll fall for that again?

282
00:17:13,917 --> 00:17:19,667
Don't you dare start with that 'Prince
from another planet' nonsense again.

283
00:17:20,417 --> 00:17:21,792
I don't believe you!

284
00:17:21,917 --> 00:17:23,292
Wooju… be polite to the Prince.

285
00:17:23,417 --> 00:17:25,000
Hachi.

286
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,625
I'd like one signature Moon Bread.

287
00:17:38,583 --> 00:17:40,083
Card, please.

288
00:17:42,167 --> 00:17:44,750
Sure. Enjoy.

289
00:17:44,875 --> 00:17:46,125
Thanks for your hard work.

290
00:17:46,250 --> 00:17:47,125
Welcome!

291
00:17:47,250 --> 00:17:49,292
Can I have one Star Bread and one Moon
Bread?

292
00:17:58,542 --> 00:18:00,083
Enjoy.

293
00:18:08,125 --> 00:18:09,583
Raon.

294
00:18:10,250 --> 00:18:11,250
Yeah?

295
00:18:11,375 --> 00:18:15,542
Have you really seen that bread before?

296
00:18:16,042 --> 00:18:22,125
Yeah, I ate it all the time back home.

297
00:18:25,708 --> 00:18:32,000
Are you and my dad… really from the same
place?

298
00:18:32,125 --> 00:18:34,375
Didn't I tell you?

299
00:18:34,750 --> 00:18:36,500
We're from the same place, that's how I
know him.

300
00:18:36,625 --> 00:18:38,333
I still don't believe you.

301
00:18:38,708 --> 00:18:40,125
You'll believe me eventually.

302
00:18:43,958 --> 00:18:46,708
Everyone, listen up!

303
00:18:47,292 --> 00:18:50,375
We have Star Bread here.

304
00:18:51,292 --> 00:18:53,625
It's the best bread in the universe.

305
00:18:54,125 --> 00:18:57,458
Made by the greatest baker in the
universe.

306
00:18:58,250 --> 00:19:02,250
Many lovely people live here.

307
00:19:02,375 --> 00:19:05,708
Friends, family, and lovers.

308
00:19:05,833 --> 00:19:07,625
And companions.

309
00:19:09,792 --> 00:19:11,875
The taste of this Star Bread…

310
00:19:19,583 --> 00:19:21,542
is the sweetness of love.

311
00:19:30,083 --> 00:19:32,042
And what about the taste of the sun?

312
00:19:33,458 --> 00:19:35,583
It's the warmth of comfort.

313
00:19:38,042 --> 00:19:40,000
And the taste of the moon?

314
00:19:44,917 --> 00:19:48,458
It's the soft, warm feeling of happiness.

315
00:19:53,042 --> 00:19:54,292
Dad…

316
00:20:58,917 --> 00:21:00,667
What are you looking at?

317
00:21:05,083 --> 00:21:06,667
The stars…

318
00:21:09,875 --> 00:21:11,417
Stars?

319
00:21:13,750 --> 00:21:20,750
My parents… they must be somewhere
out there in that starry sky.

320
00:21:33,292 --> 00:21:34,958
No.

321
00:21:36,208 --> 00:21:37,625
Huh?

322
00:21:39,750 --> 00:21:41,542
They're right here.

323
00:21:44,167 --> 00:21:45,875
In this home.

324
00:21:49,750 --> 00:21:51,792
In this room.

325
00:21:54,417 --> 00:21:56,292
Even under the covers.

326
00:21:59,083 --> 00:22:00,958
They're right by your side.

327
00:22:01,083 --> 00:22:03,750
And in every loaf of bread.

328
00:22:07,250 --> 00:22:10,000
They're always watching over you.

329
00:22:17,875 --> 00:22:22,292
Why are you looking at me like that?

330
00:22:26,583 --> 00:22:28,375
Are you…

331
00:22:33,250 --> 00:22:35,125
Are you leaving?
